incident descriptio: [ICC002] SALESFORCE SERVICE CLOUD - DI PAOLO, ANTONIO / ORO FF IB32332389 - NO SE VUELCA E-MAIL
assigned organization: ISSUE: ICC005: the email address is not populated in Salesforce for customer '5534172’, even though email in present in ATOS. ANALYSIS: We have checked in MDM database and found that this email is showing as INVALID email and hence not getting populated to downstream system. Also we have identified that 4-5 times same email was processed as VALID email through MDM. This needs to be investigate further why MDM/IDQ email validation is working differently for same email address. BUSINESS IMPACT: Due to this email is not populated in downstream system and customer is not able to see his/her updated email in Salesforce. This is creating a data discrepancy between upstream and downstream system. RESOLUTION: We have reprocessed the record with email address as 'valid' and same has been populated to downstream system. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: Yes(PBI000000085157), this is an issue and need to investigate it further. CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: Yes, once fix will be deployed against the PR which we have raised for this issue.

incident descriptio: [NDCSUPPORT] ERRORES EN SERVICIOS POR COMUNICACIÓN EN RESIBER

assigned organization: Issue: KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FICHERO OFFLINE_ENROLMENT (Comarch --> Iberia Cards) KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO PARTIAL_REVERSAL_20201022_08_27_28_IBC.trn KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO IB_CARD_ASSIGMENT Analysis: Analyzed the issue and found that we have not received the files in the below location that's why load plan got failed. files directory: /obhcip/input/comarch Business Impact: Delay in file execution will impact Iberia cards since it holds Reversal points data, consumed by partners of the loyalty program and hence the users will not be able to see the updated Reversal points against their Iberia Cards. Resolution: Re ran the ODI Load plan for Partial Reversal file to successfully process the file. PKG_OFFLINE_ENROLMENT_out PKG_FISION_FICHEROS_PARTIAL_REVERSAL_trn_out PKG_FISION_FICHEROS_IB_CARD_ASSIGMENT_trn_out CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. The File was delayed from the source Team and therefore, no issue with the application. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: No. As the files are received from the source Team. There was delay in sending the files due to which the load Plan failed.

incident descriptio: [CARGO PORTAL]Track & Trace is not showing the latest information of a booking INC0131274
assigned organization: [Issue]:Track & Trace is not showing the latest information of a booking AWB [Impact]:user will not able to see AWB details over the track and trace screen. [Analysis]:As per system design we receive FSU messages from BA80/Ciber and we process it and later stored into database but as per the logic written in the code on the basis we are showing data over the screen. If the cancel status of FSU is “N” in that case you will get the info over the T&T Screen but if the cancel status is “Y” then you will get the info over the screen. (Hope this will help). I have checked this shipment (075-49161265 ) where we have received BKD messages with cancel status “S” due to which that are not appearing on T&T Screen. [Step Taken to Resolve]:we have shared our anayzed with user and he has confirmed to closed the issue. [Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No).]:No [Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No)]:No

incident descriptio: Incidencia falta de información en ICAR
assigned organization: Issue: ICAR could not find email_marketing value for many user in their system. Analysis: As MDM is a data warehousing system, it can get updates on a single Golden ID with multiple sources and though it records all the updates in MERGES file but the latest update on the particular Golden Ids are sent to the downstream system (i.e. ICAR), irrespective of source system. In this scenario following conditions can affect the population of email_marketing for the mentioned Golden Ids : • When the Golden Ids receive updates from source IBCOM, the email_marketing is fetched and populated. • For the same Ids when it receives updates from any other source like RESTKT or RESCHK, the email_marketing will be detached and the Golden Ids will be sent downstream with null email_marketing which then updates it in ICAR. • It remains null until next update from IBCOM source comes on the Golden ids. • In MDM updates from different source is a frequent and known phenomena but as ICAR loads are on weekly basis, it might not keep up with the updates on MDM and will update the records with the value of latest i.e. every Friday’s MERGES file. Business Impact: ICAR needs email_marketing field for marketing purpose for IBCOM customers, hence absence of its value may impact business. Resolution: MDM-ICAR integration was thoroughly checked and the reason for absence of email_marketing field was temporary i.e. dependent upon the update on the IBCOM records with IBCOM or other source. It was explained to ICAR. Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No) no, Problem ticket Not required. System working as designed. Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No) No, this cant be prevented as it is working as per design. ------------

Resolution: Re ran the ODI Load plan for Partial Reversal file to successfully process the file. PKG_FISION_FICHEROS_IB_CARD_ASSIGMENT_trn_out CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. The File was delayed from the source Team and therefore, no issue with the application. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: No. As the files are received from the source Team. There was delay in sending the files due to which the load Plan failed.

incident descriptio: fichero de ibplus IBP_OPERATIONSM_20201101_000000.txt no recibido para el mes de noviembre
assigned organization: ISSUE: AIP has reported that they have not received IBPLUS Monthly file for November. impact : If AIP will not receive this data ,they will not be able to generate the reports at their end required for business. Analysis : We have checked the path on exchange node where these files are sent by source at user ftpicc003ibplliveon exchange node and file was not available and we also checked the s3 bucket to make sure if the files were archived. Steps Taken to Resolve: 1.We have checked the path on exchange node where these files are sent by source at user ftpicc003ibpllive on exchange node and the files was not available. We followed-up with ATOS team for the reason for missing file. 2. ATOS confirmed that they have transferred the file correctly. 3.We again checked at the destination location for the IBPLUS files. And the files was present at the location /ibftplinint/live/ftpicc003loyalive/ . 4. we contacted AIP team to check and verify if the files are available. AIP confirmed that the files are received . Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No).: No , as the issue is related to source and target data. Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No): No , as the issue is related to source and target data.

incident descriptio: OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO PARTIAL_REVERSAL_*_IBC.trn
assigned organization: Issue: OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO PARTIAL_REVERSAL_*_IBC.trn Analysis: Analyzed the issue and found that File arrived late on 6th 07:24 and process got triggered on 5th Aug 22:25 hence the load plan failed. files directory: /obhcip/input/comarch Business Impact: Delay in file execution will impact Iberia cards since it holds Reversal points data, consumed by partners of the loyalty program and hence the users will not be able to see the updated Reversal points against their Iberia Cards. Resolution: Re ran the ODI Load plan for Partial Reversal file to successfully process the file. PKG_FISION_FICHEROS_PARTIAL_REVERSAL_trn_out CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. The File was delayed from the source Team and therefore, no issue with the application. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: No. As the files are received from the source Team. There was delay in sending the files due to which the load Plan failed.

assigned organization: El activo asociado con el material FW18415: K0680 no tiene ninguna cantidad por montaje. Ésta es la razón de este error. Pudimos ver que se realizaron 561 movimientos de material en el almacén YM57. Tenga en cuenta que esta clase de movimiento no se debe utilizar en el sistema de producción para crear una cantidad. Después de esto, se movió a Z000 usando el movimiento 311. Debido al movimiento 561, no hay una cantidad alta en el activo 3200004261. El movimiento 261, 262, 9M1, 9D2, 101 y 102 tiene el efecto en el activo pero no en ningún otro movimiento. La forma correcta en este caso fue, 9M1 realiza en 22/10/2020 debe desmontarse con el movimiento 9D2, que haría alta la cantidad y valor de los activos.

Issue: KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FICHERO OFFLINE_ENROLMENT (Comarch --> Iberia Cards) KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO PARTIAL_REVERSAL_20201022_08_27_28_IBC.trn KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO IB_CARD_ASSIGMENT Analysis: Analyzed the issue and found that we have not received the files in the below location that's why load plan got failed. files directory: /obhcip/input/comarch Business Impact: Delay in file execution will impact Iberia cards since it holds Reversal points data, consumed by partners of the loyalty program and hence the users will not be able to see the updated Reversal points against their Iberia Cards. Resolution: Re ran the ODI Load plan for Partial Reversal file to successfully process the file. PKG_OFFLINE_ENROLMENT_out PKG_FISION_FICHEROS_PARTIAL_REVERSAL_trn_out PKG_FISION_FICHEROS_IB_CARD_ASSIGMENT_trn_out CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. The File was delayed from the source Team and therefore, no issue with the application. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: No. As the files are received from the source Team. There was delay in sending the files due to which the load Plan failed.
Se comprueba acceso tras desbloqueo.

assigned organization: Order's header text and operation text contains special character ( " ). Above caused the issue while printing. In the future please make sure that the order header text and the operation text do not contain special characters in AMOS / SAP to avoid print order problems. incident descriptio: [CARGO PORTAL]: DEP(ACC) message was not received in C2K [CIQSUP-1430]
assigned organization: Closure Comment ================ [Issue]- DEP(ACC) message was not received in C2K. [Impact]- DEP performance will get impacted. [Analysis] - We have raised with BA80 team to know the reason of not received DEP message for ACC station. [Step Taken to Resolve] ->We have checked with BA80 team to know the reason of DEP was not received in C2K. The FFM from ACC included a special handling code CSL which does not show as valid in BA80 which was the reason for no BA80 FSU DEP for the ACC sector and we shared the all the info to user as below I believe that you got the reason the answer and nothing is now pending reacted to the subject. We are going to close the issue. [Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No)] - NA ====================

Issue: KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FICHERO OFFLINE_ENROLMENT (Comarch --> Iberia Cards) KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO PARTIAL_REVERSAL_20210111_08_27_28_IBC.trn KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO IB_CARD_ASSIGMENT Analysis: Analyzed the issue and found that we have not received the files in the below location that's why load plan got failed. files directory: /obhcip/input/comarch Business Impact: Delay in file execution will impact Iberia cards since it holds Reversal points data, consumed by partners of the loyalty program and hence the users will not be able to see the updated Reversal points against their Iberia Cards. Resolution: Re ran the ODI Load plan for Partial Reversal file to successfully process the file. PKG_OFFLINE_ENROLMENT_out PKG_FISION_FICHEROS_PARTIAL_REVERSAL_trn_out PKG_FISION_FICHEROS_IB_CARD_ASSIGMENT_trn_out CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. The File was delayed from the source Team and therefore, no issue with the application. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: No. As the files are received from the source Team. There was delay in sending the files due to which the load Plan failed.

incident descriptio: ADA006: PIR file for previous month is not received IB-PIR-202012.dat
assigned organization: ISSUE: ADA006: PIR file for previous month is not received IB-PIR-202012.dat ANALYSIS: We have checked PIR data was not present in Staging tables(sta_t_pires), update tables(ods_t_pires) and final tables(dds_t_pires) as we have not received the PIR file for April month. BUSINESS IMPACT: Since data was not available in OBI, users were not able to see the PIR details and loss baggage information. RESOLTUION: 1. We have created the report from OBI as we have not received the PIR file. 2. Once we have got the file, we have placed the file on the below location /ibdwjbad/jbadtx 3. we have executed below script to load the PIR data. i. /ibdwjbad/jbadadm/bin/sh/04_carga_pires.sh ii. /ibdwjbad/jbadadm/bin/sh/05_procesa_datos.sh iii. /ibdwjbad/jbadadm/bin/sh/06_exporta_envia.sh CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: NO, As File was not received from the source on time. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: NO, this is not a recurring issue.

incident descriptio: No hemos recibido el fichero de IBPLUS_Monthly para el día 12 de Enero
assigned organization: ISSUE: AIP has reported that they have not received IBPLUS Monthly file for December. impact : If AIP will not receive this data ,they will not be able to generate the reports at their end required for business. Analysis : We have checked the path on exchange node where these files are sent by source at user ftpicc003ibplliveon exchange node and file was not available and we also checked the s3 bucket to make sure if the files were archived. Steps Taken to Resolve: 1.We have checked the path on exchange node where these files are sent by source at user ftpicc003ibpllive on exchange node and the files was not available. We followed-up with ATOS team for the reason for missing file. 2. ATOS confirmed that they have transferred the file correctly. 3.We again checked at the destination location for the IBPLUS files. And the files was present at the location /ibftplinint/live/ftpicc003loyalive/ . 4. we contacted AIP team to check and verify if the files are available. AIP confirmed that the files are received . Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No).: No , as the issue is related to source and target data. Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No): No , as the issue is related to source and target data.

[SSI]: Estimado usuario, Para poder generar la incidencia por favor adjuntar el correo sospechoso en formato outlook: Para enviar un mensaje adjunto en un correo tienes que realizar las acciones siguientes: o Ir a tu bandeja de entrada y situarte encima del mensaje, de modo que quede seleccionado. o Pulsar las teclas Ctrl y C al mismo tiempo. o Abrir un nuevo correo (que será el que se envíe a ssi@iberia.es) y situar el ratón en el campo del texto del mensaje (igual que si fueses a redactar un mensaje). o Pulsar las teclas Ctrl y V al mismo tiempo. El mensaje copiado aparecerá como un fichero adjunto. (SOLO FUNCIONA EN OUTLOOK, para enviar desde OUTLOOK) Pasos para guardar EMAIL en FORMATO OUTLOOK y enviar desde OWA también Guardar email en formato Outlook desde la aplicación: Abra el mensaje que desea guardar y, en la pestaña archivo, haga clic en Guardar como. ISSUE: ICC005: New email address is not updated in Salesforce for customer '17127470',even though email was updated in ATOS. Still user is seeing the old email in salesforce. ANALYSIS: We have checked in MDM database and found that this email was updated in upstream system and passed on to the MDM input files. Due to some issue at MDM, new email was not updated in MDM database. Hence in MDM\Salesforce old email is being reflected. BUSINESS IMPACT: Due to this issue, new email is not updated in downstream system and customer is not able to see his/her updated email in Salesforce. This is creating a data discrepancy between upstream and downstream system. RESOLTUION: We have reprocessed the record with new email and same has been updated to downstream system. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: Yes(PBI000000085358), this is an issue and need to investigate further why email is not updated in MDM database. CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: Yes, once fix will be deployed against the PR which we have raised for this issue.

column21: SM OPER Y SER AL CLI EN A (APSC00)

assigned organization: issue: welcome emails are not sent to customers on the day when they are regsitered. impact: if emails are not sent correctly then this automation is of no use Analysis: All the information of customers which are available in marketing cloud are received from Salesforce service as after Phase 2, ID18 is considered as the subscriber key. ID18 is generated in Salesforce Service for all the customers, which is unique, and once a customer is added in Salesforce Service, it gets synced from Service to Marketing Cloud every 15 mins. In Salesforce service, Customer information gets inserted/updated from another source which is MDM. All the data of new customers which gets inserted in Salesforce depends upon MDM schedule which runs 6:00 PM daily.(Sometimes the scheduler takes 2-3 days as well). Files which we are receiving from ATOS every day is at 07:00 AM. At this moment of time, these newly added customers are sent by ATOS to MDM as well, are still not added in Service and hence they are not available in Salesforce Marketing Cloud as well.(Already the process to load Customers in Salesforce Marketing from Service is delayed) Thus the issue being, Account_Salesforce DE is not loaded with recent customers information, and hence all the Bienvenida customers are not queried. Resolution: We have opened a PB for further analysis and fixing the issue. Problem ticket/Change request- Yes, PBI000000085856 created for this issue. Preventive measures:No, as of now no resolution has been found.

Issue: KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FICHERO OFFLINE_ENROLMENT (Comarch --> Iberia Cards) KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO PARTIAL_REVERSAL_20210113_08_27_28_IBC.trn KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO IB_CARD_ASSIGMENT Analysis: Analyzed the issue and found that we have not received the files in the below location that's why load plan got failed. files directory: /obhcip/input/comarch Business Impact: Delay in file execution will impact Iberia cards since it holds Reversal points data, consumed by partners of the loyalty program and hence the users will not be able to see the updated Reversal points against their Iberia Cards. Resolution: Re ran the ODI Load plan for Partial Reversal file to successfully process the file. PKG_OFFLINE_ENROLMENT_out PKG_FISION_FICHEROS_PARTIAL_REVERSAL_trn_out PKG_FISION_FICHEROS_IB_CARD_ASSIGMENT_trn_out CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. The File was delayed from the source Team and therefore, no issue with the application. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: No. As the files are received from the source Team. There was delay in sending the files due to which the load Plan failed.

Issue: KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FICHERO OFFLINE_ENROLMENT (Comarch --> Iberia Cards) KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO PARTIAL_REVERSAL_20210114_08_27_28_IBC.trn KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO IB_CARD_ASSIGMENT Analysis: Analyzed the issue and found that we have not received the files in the below location that's why load plan got failed. files directory: /obhcip/input/comarch Business Impact: Delay in file execution will impact Iberia cards since it holds Reversal points data, consumed by partners of the loyalty program and hence the users will not be able to see the updated Reversal points against their Iberia Cards. Resolution: Re ran the ODI Load plan for Partial Reversal file to successfully process the file. PKG_OFFLINE_ENROLMENT_out PKG_FISION_FICHEROS_PARTIAL_REVERSAL_trn_out PKG_FISION_FICHEROS_IB_CARD_ASSIGMENT_trn_out CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. The File was delayed from the source Team and therefore, no issue with the application. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: No. As the files are received from the source Team. There was delay in sending the files due to which the load Plan failed.
Procedemos al reinicio de la contraseña del usuario tras seguir el proceso de seguridad.

ISSUE: ICC005: New email address is not updated in Salesforce for customers 'IB375709','IB1278159','IB19472315', even though email was updated in ATOS. Still user is seeing the old email in salesforce. ANALYSIS: We have checked in MDM database and found that this email was updated in upstream system and passed on to the MDM input files. Due to some issue at MDM, new email was not updated in MDM database. Hence in MDM\Salesforce old email is being reflected. BUSINESS IMPACT: Due to this issue, new email is not updated in downstream system and customer is not able to see his/her updated email in Salesforce. This is creating a data discrepancy between upstream and downstream system. RESOLTUION: We have reprocessed the record with new email and same has been updated to downstream system. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: Yes(PBI000000085358), this is an issue and need to investigate further why email is not updated in MDM database. CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: Yes, once fix will be deployed against the PR which we have raised for this issue.

incident descriptio: SIC023: KO in all daily files
assigned organization: Issue: KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FICHERO OFFLINE_ENROLMENT (Comarch --> Iberia Cards) KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO PARTIAL_REVERSAL_20210114_08_27_28_IBC.trn KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO IB_CARD_ASSIGMENT OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO GENERIC_ACCRUAL Analysis: Analyzed the issue and found that we have not received the files in the below location that's why load plan got failed. files directory: /obhcip/input/comarch Business Impact: Delay in file execution will impact Iberia cards since it holds Reversal points data, consumed by partners of the loyalty program and hence the users will not be able to see the updated Reversal points against their Iberia Cards. Resolution: Re ran the ODI Load plan for Partial Reversal file to successfully process the file. LP_DAILY_IBCARDS_IB_CARD_ASSIGMENT LP_DAILY_IBCARDS_GENERIC_ACCRUAL LP_DAILY_IBCARDS_PARTIAL_REVERSAL LP_DAILY_OFFLINE_ENROLMENT_TRN LP_DAILY_COMARCH_IB_CARD_ASSIGMENT_OUT LP_DAILY_COMARCH_GENERIC_ACCRUAL_OUT LP_DAILY_COMARCH_PARTIAL_REVERSAL_OUT LP_DAILY_OFFLINE_ENROLMENT_OUT CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. The File was delayed from the source Team and therefore, no issue with the application. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: No. As the files are received from the source Team. There was delay in sending the files due to which the load Plan failed.

incident descriptio: LINUX_sun - ERROR en APLICACI N=IBConecta, CI=HUB003. Avisar Oncall CRM mc_host=apliwebl1 mc_host_cl
assigned organization: Issue:: we are getting errors in IBCONECTA logs and alert (IBERIA CONECTA: GRUPOS UNISYS BBDD Y CRM: SE HAN PRODUCIDO ERRORES ACCEDIENDO A LA BASE DE DATOS. Comprobar datasources jdbc/ibconnectds Impact:: If error messages will not resolve on time , the application will not be able to create new connections with the database and application will not send the notification by any service. Analysis:: We check the blocking session on DB, we also checked in concerned logs for the specified errors, There are no errors now. There is sufficient memory and not blocking session. The issue happened because DBA team has bounce back the ibutf8 server due to some issue at their end. Steps Taken to Resolve:: We have monitor the IBCONECTA logs after raising an incident to WebLogic team, everything is fine at their end then we have contacted DBA's for the same they bounced the ibutf8 due to which alert has generated. Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No).:: No, because this is a pseudo alarm and this is handled internally by the system, we need this as it monitors the error in advance and sends us alarm as incidents. Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No) :: No, This is an alarm which is raised by the system and is handled internally, but we need to look if the handler is not done, which is not the case here.

Issue : User OB20284083 when tryin g to make a redemption from CIP Call Center application, error code received is 1011. Impact : User will not be able to make the redemptions for the bookings made. Analysis : We checked in logs of the application and from SOAP tests, we were getting error code as response <errCode>1011</errCode> <errDesc>There is no award for the scheme operator, marketing airline and booking class provided</errDesc> we verified the same with COMARCH and they informed that it is not a defect but a valid error based on the Redemption Awards setup under Admin portal. no redemption awards setup for the class X in the bookings Resolution : We told the user that it is not a defect but a valid error based on the Redemption Awards setup under Admin portal. no redemption awards setup for the class X in the bookings Can this issue be Prevented : No, this was a temporary issue where the user was not aware of the reason for the error response. Problem Ticket Required : No, this was a temporary issue which is now resolved.
Se comprueba acceso tras desbloqueo.

assigned organization:

A las 18:44:31 , vemos que el PNR si tiene el elemento OSI: Time stamp of record 2021-01-14 1844:31 OUT Runid: *14LT7 Trx code: PXSVRI PID: 0 Date: 21-01-14 Time: 1744:31 99063132*TSC__IB

KXLS1/RP/M ADIB/KXLS1/MAD170/78222826/MAD/IB/A/ES//SU 1.RAMCHANDANIRAMCHANDANI/KISHORE 2. IB5655 V 15JAN TFNBCN HK1 0700 1120 *ET* *VY3215X* 3.CT/T VIAJES TUBILLETE SL T/0034922151251 4.CT/T R/VALENTINATAROCO 5.CT/TE INTERNET//TUBILLETE.COM 6.T 7.SSR CTCE IB HK1 /INTERNET//TUBILLETE.COM/ES 8.SSR CTCM IB HK1 /0034922151251/ES 9.SSR FOID IB HK/ NI43845529P/P1 10.SSR PCTC IB HK/ NOT INFORMED/ES.EMERGENCY CONTACT NOT INFORMED 11.OSI YY AGENCIAS 12.OSI YY NDCPNR 13.OSI IB POSI-TCIBCN-Cxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx2001 14.OSI IB POSI-TPNR//78222826/I/PUBLICO +

Y a continuación vemos que a las 18:44:32 ya NO lo tiene:

Time stamp of record 2021-01-14 1844:32 OUT Runid: *14MQK Trx code: PXSVRI PID: 0 Date: 21-01-14 Time: 1744:32 99063138*TSC__IB

KXLS1/ RP/MADIB/KXLS1/MAD170/78222826/MAD/IB/A/ES//SU 1.RAMCHANDANIRAMCHANDANI/KISHORE 2. IB5655 V 15JAN TFNBCN HK1 0700 1120 *ET* *VY3215X* 3.CT/T VIAJES TUBILLETE SL T/0034922151251 4.CT/T R/VALENTINATAROCO 5.CT/TE INTERNET//TUBILLETE.COM 6.T 7.SSR CTCE IB HK1 /INTERNET//TUBILLETE.COM/ES 8.SSR CTCM IB HK1 /0034922151251/ES 9.SSR FOID IB HK/ NI43845529P/P1 10.SSR OTHS IB FOID INVALID NUMBER OF SERVICES 11.SSR OTHS IB VUELING RECORD LOCATOR LFJR3D 12.SSR PCTC IB HK/ NOT INFORMED/ES.EMERGENCY CONTACT NOT INFORMED 13.OSI YY AGENCIAS 14.OSI YY NDCPNR +

Analysis : We reported the case to COMARCH and for further investigation, they needed information as below: 1. In what format are you receiving the new password, please provide an example. 2. If the new password is received in form of a link, is this an issue of link expiry before it is used. Resolution : We asked the user for the required information. incident descriptio: KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO PARTIAL_REVERSAL_20210121_08_27_28_IBC.trn
assigned organization: Issue: KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO PARTIAL_REVERSAL_20210121_08_27_28_IBC.trn Analysis: Analyzed the issue and found that we have not received the files in the below location that's why load plan got failed. files directory: /obhcip/input/comarch Business Impact: Delay in file execution will impact Iberia cards since it holds Reversal points data, consumed by partners of the loyalty program and hence the users will not be able to see the updated Reversal points against their Iberia Cards. Resolution: Re ran the ODI Load plan for Partial Reversal file to successfully process the file. LP_DAILY_COMARCH_PARTIAL_REVERSAL_OUT CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. The File was delayed from the source Team and therefore, no issue with the application. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: No. As the files are received from the source Team. There was delay in sending the files due to which the load Plan failed.

incident descriptio: [IPM003] SAP_ALMAEN SAP NO REFLEJADO EN ORs
assigned organization: As part of motor induction, the following activities must be completed prior to motor maintenance activities. ZPINM: motor phase in ZIALMA: motor induction in YM00 (induction storage place) VA01 - Sales order creation (this will automatically create the project and the WBS) IWR1 - Revision Creation ZIALMA: link the revision and move the engine to the actual storage location In our current situation, it is clear that the motor has not been properly inducted. Even if the engine is kept in a storage location based on the equipment level, the system will still determine the storage location based on its induced data against the respective revision So please follow the necessary process correctly and try to work on this engine. The system is behaving according to the existing logic. Also note that all the above steps are very important so that this engine can be processed later using ziedu2, ZIV, ZIALB4. We did not get any response from the user after several attempts and also we have provided clarification for the issue mentioned by the user. we are proceeding to close the incident by reducing the priority to low.

Issue: KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FICHERO OFFLINE_ENROLMENT (Comarch --> Iberia Cards) KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO PARTIAL_REVERSAL_20210114_08_27_28_IBC.trn Analysis: Analyzed the issue and found that we have not received the files in the below location that's why load plan got failed. files directory: /obhcip/input/comarch Business Impact: Delay in file execution will impact Iberia cards since it holds Reversal points data, consumed by partners of the loyalty program and hence the users will not be able to see the updated Reversal points against their Iberia Cards. Resolution: Re ran the ODI Load plan for Partial Reversal file to successfully process the file. PKG_OFFLINE_ENROLMENT_out PKG_FISION_FICHEROS_PARTIAL_REVERSAL_trn_out CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. The File was delayed from the source Team and therefore, no issue with the application. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: No. As the files are received from the source Team. There was delay in sending the files due to which the load Plan failed.

incident descriptio: Hi Team, We have not receiving dynatrace alerts for long.kindly check.
assigned organization: Hello All, Please find the summary of this issue below: 1st of all this incident doesn’t qualify for Sev 2 as the Dynatrace query was stopped working since “08-Jan-21 03:20 PM” and the alert was not working for past 20 days, also BEM alerts for other applications are working as expected Dynatrace query in Splunk is written in such a way that “hostFilterStatus” flag in “serverDefinition” table in OASIS should pass the value as ‘all’ OR ‘live’ But Splunk has received the value as ‘splunk’ which is wrong because of which Splunk has not process the alerts It has happened due to 2 reasons as mentioned below: ‘serverDefinition’ table should always have value as ‘all’ OR ‘live’ for live based servers Splunk query should have point to ‘serverModelling’ table rather than ‘serverDefinition’ table. But from the 1st place(since 2018) it is pointing to ‘serverDefinition’ table (which is wrong) because of which 1st record of the search results is picked up But we are not too sure on why the 'hostFilterStatus' value is returned as 'splunk' from '08-Jan-21'. As Pankaj mentioned only C00343313 change was implemented. This needs further analysis. There are 2 ways to fix this issue. 1) Update the 'hostFilterStatus' in 'serverDefinition' table in 1300+ records 2) Update Dynatrace splunk query to pick the 'hostFilterStatus' from 'serverModelling' table. Option 2 is quick and prominent. Hence we have applied this fix and Ops team confirmed that alerts are coming through in BEM.

[Analysis] - We have investigated and found that we have received 3 booking messages and that are appearing on track and trace screen. Regarding the below information , we have checked in code and also have checked in the database as well where we haven’t received the latest FWB message for 28th Jan ,21 against this shipment 125- 68676344 that is why user is not getting the correct information over the screen. As per the functionality of code , the above information is appearing on the basis of FWB Message which indicates that above highlighted origin and destination but we haven’t received (latest FWB message for this shipment 125-68676344 ) in our system , Hence it’s not appearing over the Track and Trace Screen. [Step Taken to Resolve] ->User has confirmed to closed the issue. [Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No)] - NA ====================
